"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"–":"Zesnulý","–Male":"Zesnulý","–Female":"Zesnulá","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"okolo 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"–":"Afdød","–Male":"Afdød","–Female":"Afdød","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"omkring 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"–":"Overleden","–Male":"Overleden","–Female":"Overleden","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"circa 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"–":"Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"about 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Jennens","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Jennings  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Jennings","meanings":["English: variant of   Jenning  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","German: patronymic from a pet form (see   Jenning  ) of the personal name <i>Johannes</i> (see   John  )."]}]},{"name":"Charles","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Germanic word, <i>karl</i>, meaning ‘free man’, akin to Old English <i>ceorl</i> ‘man’. The name, Latin form <i>Carolus</i>, owed its popularity in medieval Europe to the Frankish leader  Charlemagne  (  ?742–814 ), who in  800  established himself as Holy Roman Emperor. His name (Latin <i>Carolus Magnus</i>) means ‘Charles the Great’. <i>Carolus</i>—or <i>Karl</i>, the German form—was a common name among Frankish leaders, including Charlemagne's grandfather  Charles Martel  (  688–741 ). <i>Charles</i> is the French form. The name occurs occasionally in medieval Britain as <i>Karolus</i> or <i>Carolus</i>; it had a certain vogue in West Yorkshire from the 1400s, particularly among gentry families. The form <i>Charles</i> was chosen by  Mary Queen  of Scots (  1542–87 ), who had been brought up in France, for her son, <i>Charles James</i> (  1566–1625 ), who became  King James VI  of Scotland and, from  1603 ,  James I  of England. His son and grandson both reigned as  King Charles , and the name thus became established in the 17th century both in the Stuart royal house and among English and Scottish supporters of the Stuart monarchy. In the 18th century it was to some extent favoured, along with   James  , by Jacobites, supporters of the exiled Stuarts, opposed to the Hanoverian monarchy, especially in the Highlands of Scotland. In the 19th century the popularity of the name was further enhanced by romanticization of the story of ‘Bonnie Prince Charlie’, leader of the  1745  rebellion."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Philip","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Charles Philip Jennens was born as the son of Robert Jennens. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Dianna Boyer."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"umbes 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"noin 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"environ 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Charles Philip Jennens est né, fils de Robert Jennens. Il a eu au moins 2 fils et 1 fille avec Dianna Boyer."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"um 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Charles Philip Jennens wurde, als Sohn von Robert Jennens geboren. Er hatte mit Dianna Boyer mindestens 2 Söhne und 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","–Male":"Desede","–Female":"Desede","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"about 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","–Male":"elhunyt","–Female":"elhunyt","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"1481 körül","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Anglia, United Kingdom"},"id":{"–":"Telah Meninggal","–Male":"TelahMeninggal","–Female":"TelahMeninggal","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"sekitar 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Inggris, United Kingdom"},"it":{"–":"Deceduto","–Male":"Deceduto","–Female":"Deceduta","1481–1544":"1481–1544","ABT 1481":"circa 1481","1544":"1544","1481":"1481","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Inghilterra, Regno Unito","lifeSummary":"Charles Philip Jennens è nato il come figlio di Robert Jennens. Lui avuto almeno 2 figli e 1 figlia con Dianna Boyer."},"ja":{"–":"死亡","–Male":"死亡","–Fe